description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A great opportunity has opened up within Cardio-respiratory investigations! We are looking for a new ECG Technician. Experience is desirable but not essential as full training will be provided.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Main duties involve performing Electrocardiograms (ECG’s), fitting Ambulatory Holter and Blood pressure monitors, assisting in Exercise Tolerance Testing (ETT) and helping prepare patients for Cardiac MRI tests which involves cannulation (full training will be given). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be based in Cardio-respiratory Investigations but you may be required to perform these tests across the whole of the KGH site.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a great oppertunity to build a strong foundation within Cardiology with full training given, there is the possiblity for further opportunities within the department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Leanne Kelly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Principal Cardiac Physiologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address leanne.kelly1@nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01536492542&lt;/p&gt;
